sentences: Kas sa tead, mis on muust?
context: The Estonian word 'muust' is an elative case form of the pronoun 'muu', meaning 'other'. It indicates coming out from or away from something else. This grammatical case (elative) shows movement or origin from within a place or thing. In English, it can be translated as 'other than', 'apart from', or 'besides' when indicating exclusion or difference.
